sx.blah.discord.util.audio

Class AudioPlayer

  • java.lang.Object
    • sx.blah.discord.util.audio.AudioPlayer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAudioProvider

    public class AudioPlayer
extends Object
implements IAudioProvider
    This is a general purpose audio player. This wraps the provided IAudioManager. So if you are using this, it is recommended (all though not necessary) to not interact with the audio manager after an AudioPlayer instance is created. AudioPlayer also dispatches events. These events are located in the sx.blah.discord.util.audio.events package. NOTE: The goal of this class is to provide a wide variety of tools which works on a wide variety of use-cases. As such, the feature set has a wide breadth but not necessarily depth.

      • getAudioPlayerForGuild

        public static AudioPlayer getAudioPlayerForGuild(IGuild guild)
        This gets an AudioPlayer instance for the given IGuild. It will first attempt to find an injected player instance cached in an internal map, otherwise it'll construct a new instance.
        Parameters:
        guild - The guild for which the player belongs.
        Returns:
        The player.

      • inject

        public void inject()
        This is used to wrap this player around the audio manager. This recreates all the internal controls and caches. NOTE: This is automatically called in the constructor, you should only manually call this if clean() was previously called.

      • clean

        public void clean()
        This removes all references of this player from the IAudioManager this is associated to. It additionally loads the previously used IAudioProvider and IAudioProcessor. NOTE: You will need to call inject() if you wish to use this player instance again.

      • clear

        public void clear()
        This clears the current playlist. It should be noted that this closes the stream that provides the audio to each AudioPlayer.Track object (if it exists). Which prevents these objects from being reused reliably.

      • provide

        public byte[] provide()
        Description copied from interface: IAudioProvider
        This is called to retrieve the actual audio data. This should attempt to return 20 ms of data. The audio must also respect the encoding type returned by IAudioProvider.getAudioEncodingType().
        Specified by:
        provide in interface IAudioProvider
        Returns:
        The audio data.

      • getChannels

        Specified by:
        getChannels in interface IAudioProvider
